<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-772-948  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 772 948.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Government Computer News  August 20 1990 v9 n17 p32(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Glo-Worm will transmit data securely over LANs, WANs. (GroupTechnologies Corp. introduces Glo-Worm secure communicationssoftware for local and wide area networks) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Masud, S.A.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Group Technologies Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Glo-Worm (Data security software) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Data SecurityCommunications SoftwareLocal Area NetworksWide Area NetworksEncryptionProduct IntroductionSecurity Software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Glo-Worm Will Transmit Data Securely Over LANs, WANsandM;Group Technologies Corp. has announced Glo-Worm, a product for transmittingsensitive but unclassified data securely over local or wide area networks.andM;Bill Nasuti, a senior marketing representative for the Tampa, Fla., companysaid that although currently there is only a prototype unit, he expects theproduct will be available during the first quarter of next year.andM;Company officials said Glo-Worm is based on the Data Encryption Standardalgorithm and uses public key encryption techniques for generating andmanaging encryption keys.andM;They said that in a typical situation Glo-Worm, which weighs approximately 2pounds, connects to a computer's RS-232C port and allows users to encryptinformation with a simple command.andP;  They plan to incorporate in the unit a9,600-bit/sec Hayes-compatible modem for transmitting encrypted informationover a public switched network.andM;Using the product in LAN/WAN configuration would require attaching oneGlo-Worm unit to each network through a server, they said.andP;  Each PC networknode would then access Glo-Worm via what officials call the remote usermodule.andM;Each user must get a personalized and coded key for accessing either theremote user module or Glo-Worm, they said.andM;Nasuti said Glo-Worm carries an evaluation unit price of $2,995, and theremote user module an evaluation unit price of $500.andP;  He said a printedcircuit board version is planned for PCs.andO;</TEXT></DOC>